'Stayed 2 nights in this Hotel Oct 2011. Worth paying for the seaview as the view was spectacular. We had room 501....huge terrace. Staff friendly....I dont know if they speak English as I spoke in Spanish to them?? Basic but well worth the money. Location wise it is 2 minutes to the Old town. Very quiet at night...I actually pulled the mattress off the bed and slept on the terrace listening to the sea...how nice..! I agree, No aircon or fans (although a fan might be provided in heat of the summer?) I Would reccomend this Hotel and would definatly stay again. 2 star accommodation with a 5 star view.. . Room Tip: Sea view side is facing away from the town and therefore quieter and for 10 Euros extra (for 2 night... See more room tips'